questionTemplates.text:
W: You seem very tired recently.
M: It's my new course. My teacher is very strict with me. What's more, there are many assignments every day. I spend most of my time on them.
{a}

M: Miss Zhao, do I have to finish the report today?
W: Yes, the manager wants to see it before the meeting.
{a}

W: Why only one piece of bread? You are not dieting, are you?
M: It's not diet. It's just that I don't eat much at this time of day.
{a}

M: Do you like football?
F: Yes, but I like basketball better than football.
{a}

W: You should have a look at the new MP4 player over there. It's a new design and it comes in four colors: light green, dark blue, black and brown.
M: Blue is popular with boys, but I would prefer a green one.
{a}

M: Yes, Mrs. Smith. What can I do for you? Is it the refrigerator again?
W: No, it is the oven this time. I think something is wrong with the temperature control. Whatever I try to cook gets burned.
{a}

W: I saw Tom around the corner just now. Guess what he was doing.
M: I am sure he was chatting with the postman. He seems to like the postman very much.
{a}

M: Do you think I could borrow your dictionary this weekend? I don't know some words in the paper.
W: Sorry. Normally I'd say yes, but I'm going to use it myself.
{a}

W: Why are you late?
M: I'm sorry, but next time I'll be in time to have classes.
{a}

W: I am going to Martha's house. I have a paper to complete. And I need to use her computer.
M: Why don't you buy one yourself? Think how much time you could save.
{a}

W: Are you really leaving for Hongkong, Bob?
M: I guess so. I've got my ticket and I am anxious to see Tom there on Saturday.
{a}

W: What would you like for lunch?
M: Pizza and orange juice.
{a}

M: Excuse me! I just need to send this letter the fastest way possible.
W: Let's see. We have overnight business service. That takes just two days.
{a}

M: I have to go to Professor Hudson's place to discuss my thesis. But if time allowed, I'd go to the movies with you when I come back the dorm.
W: It's too bad. I am going to the cinema right now with Jane, and I don't think you could make it.
{a}

M: Why are you so tired?
W: It has been a really busy week. Students have been checking out so many books. This always happens around examination time.
{a}

M: Is this made of metal and wood?
W: No. It's made of metal and glass.
{a}

M: Do you mind turning down the radio? I am doing my homework.
W: No, of course not.
{a}

M: We will have a party at Mary's cafe on Sunday. Would you like to join us?
W: Really? I'm glad you invite me. That's a great chance for us to talk about the old days.
{a}

W: I've noticed that you got some letters from Canada. Would you mind saving the stamps for me? My sister collects them.
M: My classmates already asked for them.
{a}

M: Have you finished your homework?
W: No, I really don't know how to do it.
{a}

W: The book is $ 8, but I have only $ 5.
M: I can lend you $ 2. That's all I have.
{a}

W: Is Aunt Margaret in? I have got something important to tell her.
M: Sorry, Mom has gone shopping. She won't be back until noon. Do you want to leave a message for her so that she would call you back as soon as possible.
{a}

M: Do you have any brothers or sisters?
W: 1 have two brothers but no sisters. My parents love us very much.
{a}

M: Is Ann looking forward to going home for the summer vacation?
W: She is counting the days.
{a}

W: What do you think we need to buy for our new kitchen?
M: We've got a fridge and a dinner table already. We need some chairs.
{a}

M: You should go to see the new movie. They are going to hold it over for another two weeks.
W: Mm, normally I wouldn't, but I should as you recommend it so strongly.
{a}

W: Sorry I did not come yesterday, because I had a temperature. Could you tell me the requirement for my term paper?
M: The theme of your paper can be about business management or touring resources in China, and the length of the paper should be no less than fifteen pages.
{a}

M: The music is so beautiful that I'd like to dance. But I don't know the steps.
W: It doesn't matter. No one will be looking at us in his crowd.
{a}

W: Daddy, I have decided to give up science and go to business school.
M: Well, it is your choice as long as pay your own way, but I should warn you that not everyone with a business degree will make a successful manager.
{a}
